## Common Mistakes to Avoid

### ❌ DON'T

```markdown
# README.md

## Live Demo
Visit: https://my-app.pages.dev  ← Not deployed yet!

# package.json
{
  "homepage": "https://not-deployed.com"  ← Broken link!
}

# .github/DESCRIPTION.md
Website: https://example.com  ← Domain not set up!
```

### ✅ DO

```markdown
# README.md

## Live Demo

**Status:** Not yet deployed

To run locally:
\`\`\`bash
bun run dev
\`\`\`

# package.json
{
  "homepage": "https://github.com/username/repo#readme"  ← Works!
}

# .github/DESCRIPTION.md
Website: https://github.com/username/repo  ← Always works!

## After deployment:

## 🚀 Deployment Status

| Service | Status |
|---------|--------|
| Dashboard | [![Deployed](badge)](https://actual-url.com) |
```

## Cloudflare Pages URL Patterns

### Project Name = URL

```
Project Name: telegram-affiliate-dashboard
URL: https://telegram-affiliate-dashboard.pages.dev
```

**Common mistake:**
```
Project Name: telegram-affiliate-dashboard
Wrong URL: https://telegram-affiliate.pages.dev  ← Missing "-dashboard"!
```

### Always verify the actual URL:

1. Deploy to Cloudflare Pages
2. Check the deployment output for actual URL
3. Visit the URL to confirm it works
4. Only then add to documentation

## Environment-Specific URLs

Document all environments clearly:

```markdown
## Environments

| Environment | URL | Purpose |
|-------------|-----|---------|
| **Production** | [app.example.com](https://app.example.com) | Live production |
| **Staging** | [staging.example.com](https://staging.example.com) | Pre-production testing |
| **Preview** | Auto-generated | PR previews |
| **Local** | http://localhost:3000 | Development |
```

## Verification Script

Create a script to verify all URLs in documentation:

**scripts/verify-urls.ts**
```typescript
#!/usr/bin/env bun

const urls = [
  "https://telegram-affiliate-dashboard.pages.dev",
  "https://api.example.com",
];

console.log("🔍 Verifying deployment URLs...\n");

for (const url of urls) {
  try {
    const response = await fetch(url);
    const status = response.ok ? "✅" : "❌";
    console.log(`${status} ${url} - ${response.status}`);
  } catch (error) {
    console.log(`❌ ${url} - Failed to fetch`);
  }
}
```

Run before updating documentation:
```bash
bun run scripts/verify-urls.ts
```

## Rule Summary

**The Golden Rule:** If it's not deployed and verified, it doesn't go in the documentation.

**Checklist:**
1. ✅ Deploy first
2. ✅ Verify it works
3. ✅ Add status badge
4. ✅ Document the URL
5. ✅ Set up CI/CD
6. ✅ Add to GitHub About

**Never:**
- ❌ Add URLs before deployment
- ❌ Guess what the URL will be
- ❌ Forget to verify URLs work
- ❌ Leave broken links in documentation

**Always:**
- ✅ Use GitHub repo URL until deployed
- ✅ Add deployment status badges
- ✅ Verify URLs before documenting
- ✅ Set up automatic deployments
- ✅ Keep documentation in sync with reality
